<br>
* now that CT is a very high level zone, what are the chances of a 36 mage getting the ring needed for the quest?  Does it drop outside as well?<br>
<br>
* What is the focus effect? Joyce hinted that it does have one, but I have not been successful in finding out what exactly it is. <br>
<br>
* Is the item worth it? <br>
<br>
<br>
I don't have a lot of cash to throw around, plus the items for sale on the Rathe always seem overinflated to me ( people even sell vendor spells for double and triple the price /boggle).<br>
Any help would be appreciated!<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silinye>silinye</A> at: 12/11/02 4:46:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 9:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1124.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Its ok</span><hr size=1> 1) All (?) mobs that used to be in Cazic should now spawn outside. However they didnt want to place these mobs all over Feerrott so they put them all on the small island where the temple is...in other words, its packed. Be careful when you pull <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Last time I was around there, I noticed that alligators seemed less common than they were in Cazic before. Maybe I was looking in the wrong spot tho.<br>
<br>
2) If I remember right, there is no focus effect on the circlet. Quite sure on that.<br>
<br>
3) This is a fairly easy to get item that can serve you well for a while. However you will still need to buy (or otherwise get) a sapphire for the quest, and for that amount you MAY be able to find other items in the bazaar that are equally good.<br>
<br>
If you have fun doing quests, go for the circlet. I used mine for a long time, and never regretted doing the quest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
