<br>
First, the Ring is a very VERY rare drop! Be prepared to waste a lot of time here! (I went from 34-39 here) I didn't see THAT many either!<br>
<br>
About three alligators circle the area around the base of the ramp. I parked my bet between the two temples and just layed the smack down on them. Be warned, the greens will likely aggro you and there IS a wandering Ta Ew. Taking all four out at once can be very VERY difficult!!<br>
<br>
If you can space out the kills a bit, then the onyl real problem is the death-march. If there are Pages/Judicators etc on the temples ground and first tier, then they'll chain-heal the alligators, turning their death march into a sprint for help! It's a good idea to do a bit of chain-nuking. Don't forget to exploit the aggro rule where if two mobs are on one player (you or your pet) then the mob will only flee when VERY low on health, if at all! Usually if you pull to your pet, you won't have the trouble of healing from nearby mobs, but it can happen, so keep your manna well-stocked!<br>
<br>
Once you've broken the spawn, it's just a matter of time. ill some things from the base of the ramp and the neighbouring temples to keep yourself occupied. Leave the healers alone if you're using anything but Air. You CAN time your nukes to hit just before they'd consider healing, dropping them down to the death-march. But this is a ahrd skill to perfect.<br>
<br>
Finally, while you're here, you can pick up your torn pages of mastery from the alligators too. They're a more common drop and I wouldn't be surprised if you got all four before you even saw a ring.<br>
<br>
Since you're getting exp and soem decent loot alongside the quest items, this isn't a bad camp at all! Solo, it;s pretty easy to pick and choose what you kill and what you don't. Sometimes feigning monks are a bit of a nuisance, but that's all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good luck to you, I swapped out my runed circlet for this item and I'm still using it while saving up for an iksar hide cap!<br>
<br>
Majishia Vie &lt;Wyrd Angles&gt;<br>
56th Conjurer of Antonius Bayle<br>
